<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<body>
		<h2>HTML Forms</h2>

		<p> When submitting this form, the result will be opened in a new browser tab:</p>
	
		<p>This form will be submitted using the GET method:</p>

		<form action="/action_page.php" target="_blank" method="get">
			<label for="fname">First name:</label><br>
			<input type="text" id="fname" name="fname" value="John"><br>
			<label for="lname">Last name:</label><br>
			<input type="text" id="lname" name="lname" value="Doe"><br><br>
			<input type="submit" value="Submit">
		</form>

		<p>If you click the "Submit" button, the form-data will be sent to a page called "/action_page.php".</p>

		<hr>

		<p>This form will be submitted using the POST method:</p>

		<form action="/action_page.php" method="post">
		  <label for="fname">First name:</label><br>
		  <input type="text" id="fname" name="fname" value="John"><br>
		  <label for="lname">Last name:</label><br>
		  <input type="text" id="lname" name="lname" value="Doe"><br><br>
		  <input type="submit" value="Submit">
		</form>

		<p>After you submit, notice that, unlike the GET method, the form value is NOT visible in the address bar of the new browser tab.</p>

		<hr>

		<h1>The form autocomplete attribute</h1>

		<p>Fill in and submit the form, the reload thepage, start to fill in the form agian - and see h ow autocomplete works.</p>

		<p>Then, try to set autocomplete to "off".</p>

		<form action="/action_page.php" autocomplete="on">
			<label for="fname">First name:</label>
			<input type="text" id="fname" name="fname"><br><br>
			<label for="email">Email:</label>
			<input type="text" id="email" name="email"><br><br>
			<input type="submit">
		</form>

		<hr>

		<h1>The form novalidate attribute</h1>

		<p>The novalidate attribute indicates that the form input is not to be validated on submit:</p>

		<form action="/action_page.php">
			<label for="email">Enter your email:</label>
			<input type="email" id="email" name="email" required><br><br>
			<input type="submit">
		</form>
	</body>
</html>
